FT  06 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Bearing Power recovery
Improvements from both its Canadian and UK operations enabled Bearing Power
International, a distributor of bearings and power transmission components,
to recover from losses of Pounds 20,550 to pre-tax profits of Pounds 1.05m
in the year to September 30.
Turnover climbed 57 per cent to Pounds 38.7m (Pounds 24.6m) and earnings per
share came to 2.4p (0.5p losses). The final dividend has been stepped up to
1p (0.75p) and with current trading showing an improvement on last year, the
company said it expected to pay its first interim next year.
